                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java:119-150                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             119:    public void parse(XrefTrailerResolver resolver) throws IOException                                                                                                          
                             120:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             121:        byte[] currLine = new byte[w[0] + w[1] + w[2]];                                                                                                                         
                             122:        while (!source.isEOF() && objectNumbers.hasNext())                                                                                                                      
                             123:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             124:            readNextValue(currLine);                                                                                                                                            
                             125:            // get the current objID                                                                                                                                            
                             126:            long objID = objectNumbers.next();                                                                                                                                  
                             127:            // default value is 1 if w[0] == 0, otherwise parse first field                                                                                                     
                             128:            int type = w[0] == 0 ? 1 : (int) parseValue(currLine, 0, w[0]);                                                                                                     
                             129:            // Skip free objects (type 0) and invalid types                                                                                                                     
                             130:            if (type == 0)                                                                                                                                                      
                             131:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             132:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             133:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             134:            // second field holds the offset (type 1) or the object stream number (type 2)                                                                                      
                             135:            long offset = parseValue(currLine, w[0], w[1]);                                                                                                                     
                             136:            // third filed may hold the generation number (type1) or the index within a object stream (type2)                                                                   
                             137:            int thirdValue = (int) parseValue(currLine, w[0] + w[1], w[2]);                                                                                                     
                             138:            if (type == 1)                                                                                                                                                      
                             139:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             140:                // third field holds the generation number for type 1 entries                                                                                                   
                             141:                resolver.setXRef(new COSObjectKey(objID, thirdValue), offset);                                                                                                  
                             142:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             143:            else                                                                                                                                                                
                             144:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             145:                // For XRef aware parsers we have to know which objects contain object streams. We will store this                                                              
                             146:                // information in normal xref mapping table but add object stream number with minus sign in order to                                                            
                             147:                // distinguish from file offsets                                                                                                                                
                             148:                resolver.setXRef(new COSObjectKey(objID, 0, thirdValue), -offset);                                                                                              
                             149:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             150:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java:174-239                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             174:    private static class ObjectNumbers implements Iterator<Long>                                                                                                                
                             175:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             176:        private final long[] start;                                                                                                                                             
                             177:        private final long[] end;                                                                                                                                               
                             178:        private int currentRange = 0;                                                                                                                                           
                             179:        private long currentEnd = 0;                                                                                                                                            
                             180:        private long currentNumber = 0;                                                                                                                                         
                             181:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             182:        private ObjectNumbers(COSArray indexArray) throws IOException                                                                                                           
                             183:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             184:            start = new long[indexArray.size() / 2];                                                                                                                            
                             185:            end = new long[start.length];                                                                                                                                       
                             186:            int counter = 0;                                                                                                                                                    
                             187:            Iterator<COSBase> indexIter = indexArray.iterator();                                                                                                                
                             188:            while (indexIter.hasNext())                                                                                                                                         
                             189:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             190:                COSBase base = indexIter.next();                                                                                                                                
                             191:                if (!(base instanceof COSInteger))                                                                                                                              
                             192:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             193:                    throw new IOException("Xref stream must have integer in /Index array");                                                                                     
                             194:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             195:                long startValue = ((COSInteger) base).longValue();                                                                                                              
                             196:                if (!indexIter.hasNext())                                                                                                                                       
                             197:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             198:                    break;                                                                                                                                                      
                             199:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             200:                base = indexIter.next();                                                                                                                                        
                             201:                if (!(base instanceof COSInteger))                                                                                                                              
                             202:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             203:                    throw new IOException("Xref stream must have integer in /Index array");                                                                                     
                             204:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             205:                long sizeValue = ((COSInteger) base).longValue();                                                                                                               
                             206:                start[counter] = startValue;                                                                                                                                    
                             207:                end[counter] = startValue + sizeValue;                                                                                                                          
                             208:                counter++;                                                                                                                                                      
                             209:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             210:            currentNumber = start[0];                                                                                                                                           
                             211:            currentEnd = end[0];                                                                                                                                                
                             212:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             213:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             214:        @Override                                                                                                                                                               
                             215:        public boolean hasNext()                                                                                                                                                
                             216:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             217:            if (start.length == 1)                                                                                                                                              
                             218:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             219:                return currentNumber < currentEnd;                                                                                                                              
                             220:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             221:            return currentRange < start.length - 1 || currentNumber < currentEnd;                                                                                               
                             222:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             223:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             224:        @Override                                                                                                                                                               
                             225:        public Long next()                                                                                                                                                      
                             226:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             227:            if (currentNumber < currentEnd)                                                                                                                                     
                             228:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             229:                return currentNumber++;                                                                                                                                         
                             230:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             231:            if (currentRange >= start.length - 1)                                                                                                                               
                             232:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             233:                throw new NoSuchElementException();                                                                                                                             
                             234:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             235:            currentNumber = start[++currentRange];                                                                                                                              
                             236:            currentEnd = end[currentRange];                                                                                                                                     
                             237:            return currentNumber++;                                                                                                                                             
                             238:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             239:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Root Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                              
                                - The existing earlyabort guard in PDFXrefStreamParser sums `/Index` entries using `indexArray.getInt(i+1, 0)`, which returns a 32-bit int. Large size values                   
                             (>2^311) are truncated or clamped to 0, so the guard never triggers even when the real totalEntries is enormous. Consequently, ObjectNumbers still iterates                        
                             potentially billions of entries, causing the fuzzer to time out.                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patch Outline                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Replace all uses of `indexArray.getInt(i+1, 0)` with a true 64-bit retrieval:                                                                                                  
                                   Fetch the COSBase at position `i+1`.                                                                                                                                         
                                   Verify its a `COSInteger`; otherwise throw an `IOException` for malformed data.                                                                                             
                                   Call `((COSInteger) base).longValue()` to get the full 64-bit size.                                                                                                          
                                - Sum these 64-bit values in `totalEntries` and compare against `MAX_XREF_ENTRIES`.                                                                                              
                                - Optionally validate that each `sizeVal >= 0`, throwing an exception on negative values to prevent logic anomalies.                                                             
                                - Preserve the original flow: if `totalEntries` exceeds the cap, abort early with an `IOException`; otherwise proceed to instantiate `ObjectNumbers` and parse                   
                             entries.                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Implementation Steps                                                                                                                                                             
                                a. In PDFXrefStreamParser.java, locate the guard block immediately after the `/Index` array validation (around lines 95102).                                                    
                                b. Replace it with the following logic:                                                                                                                                          
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   private static final long MAX_XREF_ENTRIES = 1_000_000L;                                                                                                                      
                                   ...                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   // enforce maximum entries to avoid excessive computation                                                                                                                     
                                   long totalEntries = 0L;                                                                                                                                                       
                                   for (int i = 0; i < indexArray.size(); i += 2) {                                                                                                                              
                                       COSBase sizeBase = indexArray.get(i + 1);                                                                                                                                 
                                       if (!(sizeBase instanceof COSInteger)) {                                                                                                                                  
                                           throw new IOException("XRef stream must have integer in /Index array at position " + (i+1));                                                                          
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                       long sizeVal = ((COSInteger) sizeBase).longValue();                                                                                                                       
                                       if (sizeVal < 0) {                                                                                                                                                        
                                           throw new IOException("Negative XRef range size: " + sizeVal + " at position " + (i+1));                                                                              
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                       totalEntries += sizeVal;                                                                                                                                                  
                                       if (totalEntries > MAX_XREF_ENTRIES) {                                                                                                                                    
                                           throw new IOException("XRef stream too large: " + totalEntries + " entries");                                                                                         
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   // safe to construct ObjectNumbers                                                                                                                                            
                                   objectNumbers = new ObjectNumbers(indexArray);                                                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c. Remove the old `getInt(...)`based loop and integrate the above.                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Preservation of Functionality                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The core parsing logicincluding `ObjectNumbers` expansion and the `parse` loopremains untouched.                                                                             
                                - Only the prediction and earlyabort step is modified; valid PDFs with reasonable cross-reference stream sizes proceed exactly as before.                                       
                                - Negative or noninteger `/Index` entries still cause `IOException`, keeping existing error handling.                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Addressing the Timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                - By using 64-bit arithmetic, the cap now truly reflects the number of objects to parse. Malicious or pathological inputs exceeding `MAX_XREF_ENTRIES` abort                     
                             immediately, preventing billion-entry loops.                                                                                                                                        
                                - The chosen threshold (1,000,000) balances legitimate use cases and fuzzer speed. If further tuning is needed (e.g., during CI or fuzz runs), this constant can                 
                             be lowered without changing the core logic.                                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Side Effects and Mitigation                                                                                                                                                      
                                - Negligible performance overhead from the typecheck and longvalue retrieval.                                                                                                  
                                - Any malformed `/Index` entries that slipped through before will now be caught early, potentially changing the exception messagebut these were already invalid                 
                             PDFs.                                                                                                                                                                               
                                - No changes to the harness, tests, or external libraries.                                                                                                                       
                                - Existing unit and integration tests should be rerun to confirm no regressions.                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. References & Similar Patterns                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Elsewhere in PDFBox, when extracting numeric values from COSArrays, `((COSInteger) base).longValue()` is the standard pattern (e.g., in stream field                           
                             extraction). This patch aligns with those conventions.                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             With this strategy, large XRef streams are reliably detected and aborted before expensive iteration, eliminating the libFuzzer timeout without altering downstream                  
                             parsing logic.                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The initial issue is a persistent libFuzzer timeout when exercising PDF parsing code in PDFBox. A patch was attempted in PDFXrefStreamParser.java to limit the                      
                             total number of XRef entries by introducing a `MAX_XREF_ENTRIES` constant (1_000_000L) and checking the cumulative size of all ranges in the `/Index` array,                        
                             throwing an `IOException` if the limit is exceeded. After applying this patch, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout error (`ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`),                       
                             indicating that the patch did not prevent the timeout condition.                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The fuzzer run consistently terminates with `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                                       
                                - No stack trace or exception from PDFBox is shownonly the fuzzer-level timeout.                                                                                                
                                - The timeout suggests a performance or hanging issue during parsing rather than a functional crash or exception.                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Observations and Findings                                                                                                                                                        
                                - The harness entry point drives PDFXrefStreamParser via RandomAccessRead on test inputs, potentially leading to very large `/Index` arrays.                                     
                                - The code enters a loop over `indexArray.size()` in chunks of two, computing `totalEntries` and then building `ObjectNumbers`.                                                  
                                - Without bounds, extremely large index values or deeply nested loops could stall processing, triggering the fuzzer timeout.                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - File modified: `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java`                                                                                     
                                - New constant introduced at class scope:                                                                                                                                        
                                  ```java                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  private static final long MAX_XREF_ENTRIES = 1_000_000L;                                                                                                                       
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - In the constructor block that processes the `/Index` array, the following logic was added immediately after validating the array length:                                       
                                  ```diff                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  long totalEntries = 0L;                                                                                                                                                        
                                  for (int i = 0; i < indexArray.size(); i += 2)                                                                                                                                 
                                  {                                                                                                                                                                              
                                      COSBase sizeBase = indexArray.get(i + 1);                                                                                                                                  
                                      if (!(sizeBase instanceof COSInteger))                                                                                                                                     
                                      {                                                                                                                                                                          
                                          throw new IOException("XRef stream must have integer in /Index array at position " + (i + 1));                                                                         
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      long sizeVal = ((COSInteger) sizeBase).longValue();                                                                                                                        
                                      if (sizeVal < 0)                                                                                                                                                           
                                      {                                                                                                                                                                          
                                          throw new IOException("Negative XRef range size: " + sizeVal + " at position " + (i + 1));                                                                             
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      totalEntries += sizeVal;                                                                                                                                                   
                                      if (totalEntries > MAX_XREF_ENTRIES)                                                                                                                                       
                                      {                                                                                                                                                                          
                                          throw new IOException("XRef stream too large: " + totalEntries + " entries");                                                                                          
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                  }                                                                                                                                                                              
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - This enforces a ceiling of one million cumulative entries before proceeding to `new ObjectNumbers(indexArray)`.                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Result After Patch                                                                                                                                                               
                                - Re-running libFuzzer yields the same `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                                              
                                - No new exception from the added checks is observed, implying either the limit is not reached or the hang occurs elsewhere.                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - PDFXrefStreamParser.parse logic beyond the `/Index` array loop, especially `ObjectNumbers` initialization and subsequent object table construction.                            
                                - Underlying I/O in `RandomAccessRead` when scanning very large streamspossible blocking or excessive reads.                                                                    
                                - The fuzzer harness setup and invocation parameters (timeout threshold, input feeding strategy).                                                                                
                                - Other code paths in PDFParser that may iterate over large data structures (e.g., XObjects, content streams).                                                                   
                                - Resource cleanup and thread interactions in the parser that might lead to deadlock or unbounded work.                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             No solutions or root-cause hypotheses are provided herethis report only documents the issue, patch, outcome, and recommended code areas for a broader review.                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.                                                                                                                                   
                             ===Analysis Report===
