                             14: * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and                                                                                                           
                             15: * limitations under the License.                                                                                                                                                
                             16: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             17:package org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser;                                                                                                                                             
                             18:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             19:import java.io.IOException;                                                                                                                                                      
                             20:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             21:import java.util.Arrays;                                                                                                                                                         
                             22:import java.util.Iterator;                                                                                                                                                       
                             23:import java.util.NoSuchElementException;                                                                                                                                         
                             24:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             25:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSArray;                                                                                                                                           
                             26:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSBase;                                                                                                                                            
                             27:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSInteger;                                                                                                                                         
                             28:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSName;                                                                                                                                            
                             29:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSStream;                                                                                                                                          
                             30:import org.apache.pdfbox.io.RandomAccessRead;                                                                                                                                    
                             31:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObjectKey;                                                                                                                                       
                             32:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             33:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             34: * This will parse a PDF 1.5 (or better) Xref stream and                                                                                                                         
                             35: * extract the xref information from the stream.                                                                                                                                 
                             36: *                                                                                                                                                                               
                             37: *  @author Justin LeFebvre                                                                                                                                                      
                             38: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             39:public class PDFXrefStreamParser                                                                                                                                                 
                             40:{                                                                                                                                                                                
                             41:    private final int[] w = new int[3];                                                                                                                                          
                             42:    private ObjectNumbers objectNumbers = null;                                                                                                                                  
                             43:    private final RandomAccessRead source;                                                                                                                                       
                             44:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             45:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             46:     * Constructor.                                                                                                                                                              
                             47:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             48:     * @param stream The stream to parse.                                                                                                                                        
                             49:     *                                                                                                                                                                           
                             50:     * @throws IOException If there is an error initializing the stream.                                                                                                         
                             51:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             52:    public PDFXrefStreamParser(COSStream stream) throws IOException                                                                                                              
                             53:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             54:        source = stream.createView();                                                                                                                                            
                             55:        try                                                                                                                                                                      
                             56:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             57:            initParserValues(stream);                                                                                                                                            
                             58:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             59:        catch (IOException exception)                                                                                                                                            
                             60:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             61:            close();                                                                                                                                                             
                             62:            throw exception;                                                                                                                                                     
                             63:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             64:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             65:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             66:    private void initParserValues(COSStream stream) throws IOException                                                                                                           
                             67:    {                                                                                                                                                                            
                             68:        COSArray wArray = stream.getCOSArray(COSName.W);                                                                                                                         
                             69:        if (wArray == null)                                                                                                                                                      
                             70:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             71:            throw new IOException("/W array is missing in Xref stream");                                                                                                         
                             72:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             73:        if (wArray.size() != 3)                                                                                                                                                  
                             74:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             75:            throw new IOException(                                                                                                                                               
                             76:                    "Wrong number of values for /W array in XRef: " + Arrays.toString(w));                                                                                       
                             77:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             78:        for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)                                                                                                                                              
                             79:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             80:            w[i] = wArray.getInt(i, 0);                                                                                                                                          
                             81:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             82:        if (w[0] < 0 || w[1] < 0 || w[2] < 0)                                                                                                                                    
                             83:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             84:            throw new IOException("Incorrect /W array in XRef: " + Arrays.toString(w));                                                                                          
                             85:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             86:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             87:        COSArray indexArray = stream.getCOSArray(COSName.INDEX);                                                                                                                 
                             88:        if (indexArray == null)                                                                                                                                                  
                             89:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             90:            // If /Index doesn't exist, we will use the default values.                                                                                                          
                             91:            indexArray = new COSArray();                                                                                                                                         
                             92:            indexArray.add(COSInteger.ZERO);                                                                                                                                     
                             93:            indexArray.add(COSInteger.get(stream.getInt(COSName.SIZE, 0)));                                                                                                      
                             94:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             95:        if (indexArray.isEmpty() || indexArray.size() % 2 == 1)                                                                                                                  
                             96:        {                                                                                                                                                                        
                             97:            throw new IOException(                                                                                                                                               
                             98:                    "Wrong number of values for /Index array in XRef: " + Arrays.toString(w));                                                                                   
                             99:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             100:        // create an Iterator for all object numbers using the index array                                                                                                      
                             101:        objectNumbers = new ObjectNumbers(indexArray);                                                                                                                          
                             102:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             103:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             104:    private void close() throws IOException                                                                                                                                     
                             105:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             106:        if (source != null)                                                                                                                                                     
                             107:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             108:            source.close();                                                                                                                                                     
                             109:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             110:        objectNumbers = null;                                                                                                                                                   
                             111:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             112:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             113:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             114:     * Parses through the unfiltered stream and populates the xrefTable HashMap.                                                                                                
                             115:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             116:     * @param resolver resolver to read the xref/trailer information                                                                                                            
                             117:     * @throws IOException If there is an error while parsing the stream.                                                                                                       
                             118:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             119:    public void parse(XrefTrailerResolver resolver) throws IOException                                                                                                          
                             120:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             121:        byte[] currLine = new byte[w[0] + w[1] + w[2]];                                                                                                                         
                             122:        while (!source.isEOF() && objectNumbers.hasNext())                                                                                                                      
                             123:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             124:            readNextValue(currLine);                                                                                                                                            
                             125:            // get the current objID                                                                                                                                            
                             126:            long objID = objectNumbers.next();                                                                                                                                  
                             127:            // default value is 1 if w[0] == 0, otherwise parse first field                                                                                                     
                             128:            int type = w[0] == 0 ? 1 : (int) parseValue(currLine, 0, w[0]);                                                                                                     
                             129:            // Skip free objects (type 0) and invalid types                                                                                                                     
                             130:            if (type == 0)                                                                                                                                                      
                             131:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             132:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             133:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             134:            // second field holds the offset (type 1) or the object stream number (type 2)                                                                                      
                             135:            long offset = parseValue(currLine, w[0], w[1]);                                                                                                                     
                             136:            // third filed may hold the generation number (type1) or the index within a object stream (type2)                                                                   
                             137:            int thirdValue = (int) parseValue(currLine, w[0] + w[1], w[2]);                                                                                                     
                             138:            if (type == 1)                                                                                                                                                      
                             139:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             140:                // third field holds the generation number for type 1 entries                                                                                                   
                             141:                resolver.setXRef(new COSObjectKey(objID, thirdValue), offset);                                                                                                  
                             142:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             143:            else                                                                                                                                                                
                             144:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             145:                // For XRef aware parsers we have to know which objects contain object streams. We will store this                                                              
                             146:                // information in normal xref mapping table but add object stream number with minus sign in order to                                                            
                             147:                // distinguish from file offsets                                                                                                                                
                             148:                resolver.setXRef(new COSObjectKey(objID, 0, thirdValue), -offset);                                                                                              
                             149:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             150:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             151:        close();                                                                                                                                                                
                             152:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             153:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             154:    private void readNextValue(byte[] value) throws IOException                                                                                                                 
                             155:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             156:        int remainingBytes = value.length;                                                                                                                                      
                             157:        int amountRead;                                                                                                                                                         
                             158:        while ((amountRead = source.read(value, value.length - remainingBytes, remainingBytes)) > 0)                                                                            
                             159:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             160:            remainingBytes -= amountRead;                                                                                                                                       
                             161:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             162:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             163:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             164:    private long parseValue(byte[] data, int start, int length)                                                                                                                 
                             165:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             166:        long value = 0;                                                                                                                                                         
                             167:        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++)                                                                                                                                        
                             168:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             169:            value += ((long) data[i + start] & 0x00ff) << ((length - i - 1) * 8);                                                                                               
                             170:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             171:        return value;                                                                                                                                                           
                             172:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             173:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             174:    private static class ObjectNumbers implements Iterator<Long>                                                                                                                
                             175:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             176:        private final long[] start;                                                                                                                                             
                             177:        private final long[] end;                                                                                                                                               
                             178:        private int currentRange = 0;                                                                                                                                           
                             179:        private long currentEnd = 0;                                                                                                                                            
                             180:        private long currentNumber = 0;                                                                                                                                         
                             181:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             182:        private ObjectNumbers(COSArray indexArray) throws IOException                                                                                                           
                             183:        {                                                                                                                                                                       
                             184:            start = new long[indexArray.size() / 2];                                                                                                                            
                             185:            end = new long[start.length];                                                                                                                                       
                             186:            int counter = 0;                                                                                                                                                    
                             187:            Iterator<COSBase> indexIter = indexArray.iterator();                                                                                                                
                             188:            while (indexIter.hasNext())                                                                                                                                         
                             189:            {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             190:                COSBase base = indexIter.next();                                                                                                                                
                             191:                if (!(base instanceof COSInteger))                                                                                                                              
                             192:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             193:                    throw new IOException("Xref stream must have integer in /Index array");                                                                                     
                             194:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             195:                long startValue = ((COSInteger) base).longValue();                                                                                                              
                             196:                if (!indexIter.hasNext())                                                                                                                                       
                             197:                {                                                                                                                                                               
                             198:                    break;                                                                                                                                                      
                             199:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             200:                base = indexIter.next();                                                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Reapply and retain the previous XRefstream bounds checks in PDFXrefStreamParser                                                                                                 
                                - Keep the static constants MAX_W_SUM and MAX_XREF_ENTRIES and the corresponding checks on the /W array sum and processedEntries counter.                                        
                                - This ensures we still bound XRef parsing and avoid pathological O(n) hangs there.                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Instrument Type1Parser.readEncoding to guard against infinite loops                                                                                                              
                                Root cause: readEncodings two loops over the PostScript token stream (skip until dup/readonly/def and consume dup  put entries) never detect EOF or                        
                             pathological input, causing a tight infinite loop when the expected markers never appear. To fix:                                                                                   
                                a. Introduce two new constants in Type1Parser.java near the top of the class:                                                                                                    
                                   ```java                                                                                                                                                                       
                                   // in org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser                                                                                                                                    
                                   private static final int MAX_ENCODING_SKIP_TOKENS   = 10000;  // or another suitably high bound                                                                               
                                   private static final int MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES       = 256;    // typical max 256 codes in an encoding                                                                         
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                b. Replace the first unbounded skiploop (around line 217) with a bounded version that:                                                                                          
                                   - Peeks at the next token; if it is null, throws IOExceptionUnexpected EOF in Encoding.                                                                                    
                                   - If it is a NAME token and its text is one of dup, readonly, or def, break out.                                                                                        
                                   - Otherwise, consume the token and increment a skip counter; if the counter exceeds MAX_ENCODING_SKIP_TOKENS, throw IOExceptionToo many tokens before                       
                             encoding definition.                                                                                                                                                               
                                c. Replace the second unbounded duploop (around line 226) with a bounded loop that:                                                                                             
                                   - Peeks at the next token; if null or not dup, break out.                                                                                                                   
                                   - Otherwise, invoke the existing read() calls to consume dup code name put.                                                                                                
                                   - Increment an entry counter; if it exceeds MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES, throw IOExceptionToo many encoding entries.                                                              
                                This change guarantees that malformed or fuzzed PFB data cannot drive an infinite loop in readEncodingthe parser will error out promptly.                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Preserve existing logic and exception propagation                                                                                                                                
                                - The new IOException paths in readEncoding will bubble up through parseASCII and parse(), aborting font parsing and returning control to the fuzzer harness.                    
                                - StandardEncoding and properly formed encoding arrays will still be handled exactly as before (the bounds apply only when fuzz input deviates).                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. No modifications to harness, tests, or external dependencies                                                                                                                     
                                - All changes are confined to PDFXrefStreamParser.java and Type1Parser.java within the PDFBox codebase.                                                                          
                                - Harness code (PDFExtractTextFuzzer) remains untouched, preserving the existing fuzzing entry point.                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Justification and sideeffect mitigation                                                                                                                                         
                                - This approach directly addresses the observed hang in Type1Parser.readEncoding by preventing its two loops from spinning indefinitely.                                         
                                - The chosen bounds (10000 tokens skipped, 256 entries) comfortably exceed legitimate Type 1 font complexity while catching malformed/fuzz inputs early.                        
                                - Should any real-world fonts exceed these thresholds (unlikely for encoding arrays), the error can be tuned by adjusting the constants.                                         
                                - No other parser or utility is altered, minimizing risk to the broader codebase.                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Testing                                                                                                                                                                          
                                - Run the original libFuzzer target to confirm that timeouts no longer occur; instead, the fuzzer should quickly see IOExceptions for bad fonts and move on.                     
                                - Validate against a suite of known good PDFs with embedded Type 1 fonts to ensure no regressions in text extraction.                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             <code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1Parser.java:190-250</code_range>                                                                                     
                             <code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java:1-200</code_range>                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>
